  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, 20–30 dm, &lt;usually branched to base&gt;. Leaves: blade broadly rhombic, 2–4 cm &lt;widest in middle&gt;, length/width = 1.5, lobes 2–4 per side, &lt;sinuses shallow&gt;, lobe apex acute, base broadly cuneate, adaxial surface glabrous, sometimes sparsely appressed-hairy along veins. Inflorescence branches glabrous. Flowers 15–22 mm diam.; stamens 20, anthers pale pink.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering May; fruiting Sep–Oct.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Brush, successional fields, unmanaged pastures;</description>
  <description type="elevation">20–300 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ont.; Mass., Mich., N.Y., N.C., Va.</description>
  <discussion>Variety parvula is scattered through the northern range of the species and at higher elevations south into the Appalachians; it is characterized by smaller leaves that usually are very shallowly incised.</discussion>
